[2026-03-19T08:28:39.706Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Execute this requirement immediately without asking questions.\n\n## REQUIREMENT\n\n# Wire up metricsRetentionDays to purge old metrics\n\n## Metadata\n- **Category**: functionality\n- **Effort**: Medium (2/3)\n- **Impact**: Unknown (7/3)\n- **Scan Type**: feature_scout\n- **Generated**: 3/18/2026, 7:27:47 PM\n\n## Description\nThe config already defines metricsRetentionDays (default 365) but no code actually purges old daily_metrics or system_daily_metrics rows. Add a RetentionPolicy for daily_metrics keyed on the date column, and extend runRetention to delete metric rows older than metricsRetentionDays. Register daily_metrics in TABLE_REGISTRY as ephemeral with timestampColumn=date. This prevents unbounded metrics table growth.\n\n## Reasoning\nThis is a bug-level gap: the retention config exists but is dead code. daily_metrics rows accumulate forever. Products like Datadog, Prometheus, and Grafana Cloud all enforce metrics retention windows. Without this, disk usage grows linearly with time across all tenants, eventually degrading SQLite performance.\n\n\n## Recommended Skills\n\nUse Claude Code skills as appropriate for implementation guidance. Check `.claude/skills/` directory for available skills.\n\n## Notes\n\nThis requirement was generated from an AI-evaluated project idea. No specific goal is associated with this idea.\n\n## DURING IMPLEMENTATION\n\n- Use `get_memory` MCP tool when you encounter unfamiliar code or need context about patterns/files\n- Use `report_progress` MCP tool at each major phase (analyzing, planning, implementing, testing, validating)\n- Use `get_related_tasks` MCP tool before modifying shared files to check for parallel task conflicts\n\n## AFTER IMPLEMENTATION\n\n1. Log your implementation using the `log_implementation` MCP tool with:\n   - requirementName: the requirement filename (without .md)\n   - title: 2-6 word summary\n   - overview: 1-2 paragraphs describing what was done\n   - category: one of feature/bugfix/refactor/performance/security/infrastructure/ui/docs/test\n   - patternsApplied: comma-separated patterns used (e.g. \"repository pattern, debounce, memoization\")\n\n2. Verify: `npx tsc --noEmit` (fix any type errors)\n\nBegin implementation now."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"239ea274-e4d5-4daf-b79f-4e16f4e4e93b","uuid":"da0f74b8-39e8-4ff3-b10f-dda2233423b9","timestamp":"2026-03-19T08:28:39.627Z","isSynthetic":true}
