[2026-03-19T08:29:17.412Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WbrjAo4XGPVryrBm4jakQq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import crypto from 'node:crypto';\n     2→import fs from 'node:fs';\n     3→import Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n     4→import type { Logger } from 'pino';\n     5→\n     6→/** SHA-256 hash chain genesis value (64 hex zeros). */\n     7→const GENESIS_HASH = '0'.repeat(64);\n     8→\n     9→/**\n    10→ * Compute a chain hash: SHA-256(previousHash + deterministic JSON of entry fields).\n    11→ * Each entry's hash commits to the entire chain history before it.\n    12→ */\n    13→function computeChainHash(prevHash: string, entry: BufferedEntry): string {\n    14→  const payload = prevHash + JSON.stringify([\n    15→    entry.timestamp,\n    16→    entry.action,\n    17→    entry.tenantId,\n    18→    entry.actor,\n    19→    entry.resourceType,\n    20→    entry.resourceId,\n    21→    entry.detail,\n    22→    entry.ipAddress,\n    23→  ]);\n    24→  return crypto.createHash('sha256').update(payload).digest('hex');\n    25→}\n    26→\n    27→const AUDIT_SCHEMA = `\n    28→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS audit_events (\n    29→  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n    30→  timestamp TEXT NOT NULL,\n    31→  action TEXT NOT NULL,\n    32→  tenant_id TEXT,\n    33→  actor TEXT,\n    34→  resource_type TEXT,\n    35→  resource_id TEXT,\n    36→  detail TEXT,\n    37→  ip_address TEXT,\n    38→  prev_hash TEXT\n    39→);\n    40→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_audit_ts ON audit_events(timestamp);\n    41→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_audit_tenant_action_ts ON audit_events(tenant_id, action, timestamp);\n    42→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_audit_actor ON audit_events(actor);\n    43→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_audit_resource_type ON audit_events(resource_type);\n    44→DROP INDEX IF EXISTS idx_audit_tenant_ts;\n    45→DROP INDEX IF EXISTS idx_audit_action;\n    46→`;\n    47→\n    48→/** Thrown when an audit event fails to persist — signals an audit trail gap. */\n    49→export class AuditWriteError extends Error {\n    50→  constructor(\n    51→    public readonly entry: AuditEntry,\n    52→    cause: unknown,\n    53→  ) {\n    54→    super(`Audit write failed for action \"${entry.action}\"`);\n    55→    this.name = 'AuditWriteError';\n    56→    this.cause = cause;\n    57→  }\n    58→}\n    59→\n    60→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    61→// Discriminated-union audit entries — each action carries its own typed payload\n    62→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    63→\n    64→/** Fields common to every audit entry. */\n    65→interface AuditEntryBase {\n    66→  tenantId?: string;\n    67→  actor?: string;\n    68→  ipAddress?: string;\n    69→}\n    70→\n    71→// --- Key management ---\n    72→interface KeyEncryptEntry extends AuditEntryBase {\n    73→  action: 'key:encrypt';\n    74→  resourceType: 'credential';\n    75→  resourceId: string;\n    76→}\n    77→\n    78→interface KeyDecryptEntry extends AuditEntryBase {\n    79→  action: 'key:decrypt';\n    80→  resourceType: 'credential';\n    81→  resourceId: string;\n    82→}\n    83→\n    84→interface KeyDecryptFailedEntry extends AuditEntryBase {\n    85→  action: 'key:decrypt_failed';\n    86→  resourceType: 'credential';\n    87→  resourceId: string;\n    88→  detail: { reason: string };\n    89→}\n    90→\n    91→interface KeyDeleteEntry extends AuditEntryBase {\n    92→  action: 'key:delete';\n    93→  resourceType: 'credential';\n    94→  resourceId: string;\n    95→}\n    96→\n    97→interface KeyAccessEntry extends AuditEntryBase {\n    98→  action: 'key:access';\n    99→  resourceType: 'credential';\n   100→  resourceId: string;"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017AXpehDUT8ebwRaA6Z6JLX","session_id":"239ea274-e4d5-4daf-b79f-4e16f4e4e93b","uuid":"bd5b3c29-d7fc-4a77-8572-9d4265ed6e4f","timestamp":"2026-03-19T08:29:17.318Z"}
[2026-03-19T08:29:41.205Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a622d76920a46854a","tool_use_id":"toolu_017AXpehDUT8ebwRaA6Z6JLX","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore retention and metrics code","usage":{"total_tokens":38481,"tool_uses":19,"duration_ms":49740},"uuid":"9fa26274-58c7-4b06-b54f-cb52d7638343","session_id":"239ea274-e4d5-4daf-b79f-4e16f4e4e93b"}
[2026-03-19T08:29:41.205Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017AXpehDUT8ebwRaA6Z6JLX","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I have comprehensive information. Let me compile a full summary document for you.\n\n## Complete Analysis: Retention System and Metrics Tables\n\nBased on my thorough examination of the codebase, here's everything you need to understand about the retention system:\n\n---\n\n## 1. RETENTION POLICY ARCHITECTURE\n\n### RetentionPolicy Class (`/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retentionPolicy.ts`)\n\nThe `RetentionPolicy` class is a **reusable, declarative retention handler** that:\n- Takes configuration from `TABLE_REGISTRY` (single source of truth)\n- Implements a safe, chunked deletion algorithm\n- Enforces safety caps to prevent accidental data loss\n\n**Key fields:**\n- `table`: Table name (must exist in TABLE_REGISTRY)\n- `timestampColumn`: Column used to determine row age (e.g., `created_at`)\n- `maxPurgeFraction`: Safety cap (default 0.8 = 80%) — aborts if deletion would exceed this percentage\n- `chunkSize`: Rows deleted per batch (default 5000) — keeps individual lock durations ~50ms\n- `deleteFilter`: Optional SQL WHERE fragment (e.g., \"AND status IN ('completed')\")\n\n**Purge algorithm:**\n1. Count total rows in table\n2. Count candidates matching `timestamp < cutoff` AND deleteFilter\n3. If candidates/total > maxPurgeFraction, **abort with error**\n4. Delete in chunks, yielding event loop between batches to keep system responsive\n\n---\n\n## 2. TABLE REGISTRY STRUCTURE (`/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts`)\n\nThe registry defines **table lifecycle classification** as either `metrizable` or `ephemeral`:\n\n### Metrizable Tables\nTables with numeric columns worth aggregating BEFORE purge:\n\n```typescript\n{\n  lifecycle: 'metrizable',\n  table: 'persona_executions',\n  timestampColumn: 'created_at',\n  metrizableColumns: [\n    { column: 'cost_usd', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n    { column: 'duration_ms', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n    { column: 'input_tokens', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n    { column: 'output_tokens', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n  ],\n  aggregationTarget: 'daily_metrics',\n  maxPurgeFraction: 0.8,\n}\n```\n\n### Ephemeral Tables\nTables simply purged without pre-aggregation:\n\n```typescript\n{\n  lifecycle: 'ephemeral',\n  table: 'persona_events',\n  timestampColumn: 'created_at',\n  maxPurgeFraction: 0.8,\n},\n{\n  lifecycle: 'ephemeral',\n  table: 'audit_events',\n  timestampColumn: 'timestamp',\n  minRetentionDays: 90,  // Compliance floor\n  maxPurgeFraction: 0.8,\n},\n{\n  lifecycle: 'ephemeral',\n  table: 'trigger_fires',\n  timestampColumn: 'fired_at',\n  maxPurgeFraction: 0.8,\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. DATABASE SCHEMAS\n\n### DAILY_METRICS Table (per-tenant) (`/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts`)\n\nLocated in each tenant's database:\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS daily_metrics (\n  date TEXT NOT NULL,\n  total_executions INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  completed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  failed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  total_cost_usd REAL DEFAULT 0,\n  total_duration_ms INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  PRIMARY KEY (date)\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS retention_watermark (\n  key TEXT PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT 'executions',\n  last_rowid INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0\n);\n```\n\n### SYSTEM_DAILY_METRICS Table (system-wide) \n\nLocated in `system.db`:\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS system_daily_metrics (\n  date TEXT NOT NULL,\n  total_executions INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  completed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  failed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  total_cost_usd REAL DEFAULT 0,\n  total_duration_ms INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  tenant_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  aggregated_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n  PRIMARY KEY (date)\n);\n```\n\n**Key difference:** `system_daily_metrics` tracks cross-tenant aggregates and includes `tenant_count` and `aggregated_at` timestamp.\n\n---\n\n## 4. METRICS RETENTION CONFIGURATION (`/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/config.ts`)\n\nTwo configuration values control retention:\n\n```typescript\n// Retention\nretentionDays: parseInt(process.env['RETENTION_DAYS'] || '30', 10),\nmetricsRetentionDays: parseInt(process.env['METRICS_RETENTION_DAYS'] || '365', 10),\n```\n\n- **`RETENTION_DAYS`** (default 30): Age threshold for purging executions/events\n- **`METRICS_RETENTION_DAYS`** (default 365): Age threshold for purging aggregated metrics\n\n---\n\n## 5. RETENTION JOB FLOW (`/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts`)\n\n### Startup\n```typescript\nexport function startRetentionJob(\n  tenantDbManager: TenantDbManager,\n  retentionDays: number,\n  logger: Logger,\n): NodeJS.Timeout\n```\n\n**How it works:**\n- Uses **wall-clock polling** (60-second intervals) instead of drifting `setInterval`\n- Persists last run date in `system_kv` table (`retention_last_run_date`)\n- Runs **exactly once per UTC calendar day**, regardless of restarts\n- Checks 5 seconds after startup, then every 60 seconds\n\n### Purge Phase\n```typescript\nasync function runRetention(\n  tenantDbManager: TenantDbManager,\n  retentionDays: number,\n  logger: Logger,\n): Promise<void>\n```\n\nFor each tenant:\n1. Calculates `cutoff = Date.now() - retentionDays * 86,400,000`\n2. Runs `execPolicy.purge()` — deletes completed/failed/cancelled executions older than cutoff\n3. Runs `eventsPolicy.purge()` — deletes non-pending/non-processing events older than cutoff\n4. Runs `stuckEventsPolicy.purge()` — deletes stuck events older than 7× the retention window\n5. Yields event loop between tenants\n\n### Aggregation Phase\n```typescript\nfunction aggregateSystemMetrics(\n  tenantDbManager: TenantDbManager,\n  logger: Logger,\n): void\n```\n\n**Map step:** Read `daily_metrics` from every tenant database\n\n**Reduce step:** \n- Accumulate per-date totals across all tenants in memory\n- For each date, sum: `total_executions`, `completed`, `failed`, `total_cost_usd`, `total_duration_ms`\n- Count unique tenants that contributed to that date\n\n**Write step:** \n- Upsert to `system_daily_metrics` in a single transaction\n- Replaces wholesale (ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE) so system view is always consistent\n\n---\n\n## 6. AUDIT RETENTION POLICY PATTERN (`/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/auditRetentionPolicy.ts`)\n\nThis is the reference implementation for retention policy classes:\n\n```typescript\nexport class AuditRetentionPolicy {\n  private purgeTimer: NodeJS.Timeout | null = null;\n\n  constructor(\n    private auditLog: AuditLog,\n    private retentionDays: number,\n    private logger: Logger,\n  ) {\n    // MIN_AUDIT_RETENTION_DAYS = 90 (from TABLE_REGISTRY)\n    if (!Number.isFinite(retentionDays) || retentionDays < MIN_AUDIT_RETENTION_DAYS) {\n      throw new Error(\n        `auditRetentionDays must be >= ${MIN_AUDIT_RETENTION_DAYS}, got ${retentionDays}`,\n      );\n    }\n  }\n\n  async purgeOld(): Promise<number> {\n    const cutoff = new Date(Date.now() - this.retentionDays * 86_400_000).toISOString();\n    const totalDeleted = await auditPolicy.purge(this.auditLog.getDb(), cutoff, this.logger);\n    return totalDeleted;\n  }\n\n  startDailyPurge(): NodeJS.Timeout {\n    this.purgeTimer = setInterval(() => {\n      this.purgeOld().catch((err) => {\n        this.logger.error({ err }, 'Audit purge failed');\n      });\n    }, 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000);\n    return this.purgeTimer;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key patterns:**\n- Derives retention constraints from `TABLE_REGISTRY` (single source of truth)\n- Enforces minimum retention days from spec (e.g., 90 days for audit compliance)\n- Validates config on construction\n- Uses shared `RetentionPolicy` for actual purge logic\n- Provides `purgeOld()` method for manual triggering\n- Provides `startDailyPurge()` for background scheduling\n\n---\n\n## 7. KEY INSIGHTS\n\n| Aspect | Details |\n|--------|---------|\n| **Single Source of Truth** | `TABLE_REGISTRY` in shared code — all lifecycle decisions read from here, no hard-coding |\n| **Safety-First Design** | `maxPurgeFraction` prevents accidental mass deletions; aborts if > 80% would delete |\n| **Responsive Scheduling** | Wall-clock polling (60s) + event-loop yields between tenants + chunked deletes |\n| **Persistent State** | Last run date in `system_kv` ensures daily job runs exactly once per UTC calendar day |\n| **Atomicity** | Metrics aggregation uses transactions so `system_daily_metrics` view is always consistent |\n| **Typed Policy Config** | `MetrizableTableSpec` vs `EphemeralTableSpec` makes intent explicit at compile time |\n| **Minimum Retention Floors** | Configurable per table (e.g., 90 days for audit compliance) |\n\n---\n\n## 8. FILE LOCATIONS\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts` | Daily job scheduler + aggregation engine |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retentionPolicy.ts` | Reusable chunked-delete algorithm |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/auditRetentionPolicy.ts` | Reference implementation for compliance retention |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts` | **Single source of truth** for table lifecycle |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` | Schema DDL for `daily_metrics` & `system_daily_metrics` |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/config.ts` | Config loading (RETENTION_DAYS, METRICS_RETENTION_DAYS) |\n\nThis architecture cleanly separates concerns: the registry declares intent, `RetentionPolicy` implements the algorithm, `retention.ts` orchestrates the job, and `auditRetentionPolicy.ts` shows how to apply it to compliance-sensitive data."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a622d76920a46854a (use SendMessage with to: 'a622d76920a46854a' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 41331\ntool_uses: 19\nduration_ms: 49741</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"239ea274-e4d5-4daf-b79f-4e16f4e4e93b","uuid":"40b163e9-d3cc-47cc-9608-387039b3e48a","timestamp":"2026-03-19T08:29:41.127Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the existing retention system and metrics tables in this project. Please find and read these files thoroughly:\n\n1. All files related to retention: packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts, packages/orchestrator/src/retentionPolicy.ts, packages/orchestrator/src/auditRetentionPolicy.ts\n2. The config file: packages/orchestrator/src/config.ts\n3. The table registry: packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts\n4. Any database schema or migration files that define daily_metrics or system_daily_metrics tables\n5. packages/orchestrator/src/db/ directory - list contents and read key files\n6. packages/shared/src/types.ts for any metrics-related types\n\nFor each file, provide the FULL content. I need to understand:\n- How RetentionPolicy is defined and used\n- How runRetention works\n- How TABLE_REGISTRY is structured\n- What the daily_metrics and system_daily_metrics table schemas look like\n- How metricsRetentionDays is defined in config\n- The pattern used by auditRetentionPolicy as a reference implementation","agentId":"a622d76920a46854a","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I have comprehensive information. Let me compile a full summary document for you.\n\n## Complete Analysis: Retention System and Metrics Tables\n\nBased on my thorough examination of the codebase, here's everything you need to understand about the retention system:\n\n---\n\n## 1. RETENTION POLICY ARCHITECTURE\n\n### RetentionPolicy Class (`/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retentionPolicy.ts`)\n\nThe `RetentionPolicy` class is a **reusable, declarative retention handler** that:\n- Takes configuration from `TABLE_REGISTRY` (single source of truth)\n- Implements a safe, chunked deletion algorithm\n- Enforces safety caps to prevent accidental data loss\n\n**Key fields:**\n- `table`: Table name (must exist in TABLE_REGISTRY)\n- `timestampColumn`: Column used to determine row age (e.g., `created_at`)\n- `maxPurgeFraction`: Safety cap (default 0.8 = 80%) — aborts if deletion would exceed this percentage\n- `chunkSize`: Rows deleted per batch (default 5000) — keeps individual lock durations ~50ms\n- `deleteFilter`: Optional SQL WHERE fragment (e.g., \"AND status IN ('completed')\")\n\n**Purge algorithm:**\n1. Count total rows in table\n2. Count candidates matching `timestamp < cutoff` AND deleteFilter\n3. If candidates/total > maxPurgeFraction, **abort with error**\n4. Delete in chunks, yielding event loop between batches to keep system responsive\n\n---\n\n## 2. TABLE REGISTRY STRUCTURE (`/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts`)\n\nThe registry defines **table lifecycle classification** as either `metrizable` or `ephemeral`:\n\n### Metrizable Tables\nTables with numeric columns worth aggregating BEFORE purge:\n\n```typescript\n{\n  lifecycle: 'metrizable',\n  table: 'persona_executions',\n  timestampColumn: 'created_at',\n  metrizableColumns: [\n    { column: 'cost_usd', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n    { column: 'duration_ms', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n    { column: 'input_tokens', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n    { column: 'output_tokens', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n  ],\n  aggregationTarget: 'daily_metrics',\n  maxPurgeFraction: 0.8,\n}\n```\n\n### Ephemeral Tables\nTables simply purged without pre-aggregation:\n\n```typescript\n{\n  lifecycle: 'ephemeral',\n  table: 'persona_events',\n  timestampColumn: 'created_at',\n  maxPurgeFraction: 0.8,\n},\n{\n  lifecycle: 'ephemeral',\n  table: 'audit_events',\n  timestampColumn: 'timestamp',\n  minRetentionDays: 90,  // Compliance floor\n  maxPurgeFraction: 0.8,\n},\n{\n  lifecycle: 'ephemeral',\n  table: 'trigger_fires',\n  timestampColumn: 'fired_at',\n  maxPurgeFraction: 0.8,\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. DATABASE SCHEMAS\n\n### DAILY_METRICS Table (per-tenant) (`/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts`)\n\nLocated in each tenant's database:\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS daily_metrics (\n  date TEXT NOT NULL,\n  total_executions INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  completed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  failed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  total_cost_usd REAL DEFAULT 0,\n  total_duration_ms INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  PRIMARY KEY (date)\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS retention_watermark (\n  key TEXT PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT 'executions',\n  last_rowid INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0\n);\n```\n\n### SYSTEM_DAILY_METRICS Table (system-wide) \n\nLocated in `system.db`:\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS system_daily_metrics (\n  date TEXT NOT NULL,\n  total_executions INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  completed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  failed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  total_cost_usd REAL DEFAULT 0,\n  total_duration_ms INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  tenant_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  aggregated_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n  PRIMARY KEY (date)\n);\n```\n\n**Key difference:** `system_daily_metrics` tracks cross-tenant aggregates and includes `tenant_count` and `aggregated_at` timestamp.\n\n---\n\n## 4. METRICS RETENTION CONFIGURATION (`/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/config.ts`)\n\nTwo configuration values control retention:\n\n```typescript\n// Retention\nretentionDays: parseInt(process.env['RETENTION_DAYS'] || '30', 10),\nmetricsRetentionDays: parseInt(process.env['METRICS_RETENTION_DAYS'] || '365', 10),\n```\n\n- **`RETENTION_DAYS`** (default 30): Age threshold for purging executions/events\n- **`METRICS_RETENTION_DAYS`** (default 365): Age threshold for purging aggregated metrics\n\n---\n\n## 5. RETENTION JOB FLOW (`/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts`)\n\n### Startup\n```typescript\nexport function startRetentionJob(\n  tenantDbManager: TenantDbManager,\n  retentionDays: number,\n  logger: Logger,\n): NodeJS.Timeout\n```\n\n**How it works:**\n- Uses **wall-clock polling** (60-second intervals) instead of drifting `setInterval`\n- Persists last run date in `system_kv` table (`retention_last_run_date`)\n- Runs **exactly once per UTC calendar day**, regardless of restarts\n- Checks 5 seconds after startup, then every 60 seconds\n\n### Purge Phase\n```typescript\nasync function runRetention(\n  tenantDbManager: TenantDbManager,\n  retentionDays: number,\n  logger: Logger,\n): Promise<void>\n```\n\nFor each tenant:\n1. Calculates `cutoff = Date.now() - retentionDays * 86,400,000`\n2. Runs `execPolicy.purge()` — deletes completed/failed/cancelled executions older than cutoff\n3. Runs `eventsPolicy.purge()` — deletes non-pending/non-processing events older than cutoff\n4. Runs `stuckEventsPolicy.purge()` — deletes stuck events older than 7× the retention window\n5. Yields event loop between tenants\n\n### Aggregation Phase\n```typescript\nfunction aggregateSystemMetrics(\n  tenantDbManager: TenantDbManager,\n  logger: Logger,\n): void\n```\n\n**Map step:** Read `daily_metrics` from every tenant database\n\n**Reduce step:** \n- Accumulate per-date totals across all tenants in memory\n- For each date, sum: `total_executions`, `completed`, `failed`, `total_cost_usd`, `total_duration_ms`\n- Count unique tenants that contributed to that date\n\n**Write step:** \n- Upsert to `system_daily_metrics` in a single transaction\n- Replaces wholesale (ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE) so system view is always consistent\n\n---\n\n## 6. AUDIT RETENTION POLICY PATTERN (`/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/auditRetentionPolicy.ts`)\n\nThis is the reference implementation for retention policy classes:\n\n```typescript\nexport class AuditRetentionPolicy {\n  private purgeTimer: NodeJS.Timeout | null = null;\n\n  constructor(\n    private auditLog: AuditLog,\n    private retentionDays: number,\n    private logger: Logger,\n  ) {\n    // MIN_AUDIT_RETENTION_DAYS = 90 (from TABLE_REGISTRY)\n    if (!Number.isFinite(retentionDays) || retentionDays < MIN_AUDIT_RETENTION_DAYS) {\n      throw new Error(\n        `auditRetentionDays must be >= ${MIN_AUDIT_RETENTION_DAYS}, got ${retentionDays}`,\n      );\n    }\n  }\n\n  async purgeOld(): Promise<number> {\n    const cutoff = new Date(Date.now() - this.retentionDays * 86_400_000).toISOString();\n    const totalDeleted = await auditPolicy.purge(this.auditLog.getDb(), cutoff, this.logger);\n    return totalDeleted;\n  }\n\n  startDailyPurge(): NodeJS.Timeout {\n    this.purgeTimer = setInterval(() => {\n      this.purgeOld().catch((err) => {\n        this.logger.error({ err }, 'Audit purge failed');\n      });\n    }, 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000);\n    return this.purgeTimer;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key patterns:**\n- Derives retention constraints from `TABLE_REGISTRY` (single source of truth)\n- Enforces minimum retention days from spec (e.g., 90 days for audit compliance)\n- Validates config on construction\n- Uses shared `RetentionPolicy` for actual purge logic\n- Provides `purgeOld()` method for manual triggering\n- Provides `startDailyPurge()` for background scheduling\n\n---\n\n## 7. KEY INSIGHTS\n\n| Aspect | Details |\n|--------|---------|\n| **Single Source of Truth** | `TABLE_REGISTRY` in shared code — all lifecycle decisions read from here, no hard-coding |\n| **Safety-First Design** | `maxPurgeFraction` prevents accidental mass deletions; aborts if > 80% would delete |\n| **Responsive Scheduling** | Wall-clock polling (60s) + event-loop yields between tenants + chunked deletes |\n| **Persistent State** | Last run date in `system_kv` ensures daily job runs exactly once per UTC calendar day |\n| **Atomicity** | Metrics aggregation uses transactions so `system_daily_metrics` view is always consistent |\n| **Typed Policy Config** | `MetrizableTableSpec` vs `EphemeralTableSpec` makes intent explicit at compile time |\n| **Minimum Retention Floors** | Configurable per table (e.g., 90 days for audit compliance) |\n\n---\n\n## 8. FILE LOCATIONS\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts` | Daily job scheduler + aggregation engine |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retentionPolicy.ts` | Reusable chunked-delete algorithm |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/auditRetentionPolicy.ts` | Reference implementation for compliance retention |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts` | **Single source of truth** for table lifecycle |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` | Schema DDL for `daily_metrics` & `system_daily_metrics` |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/config.ts` | Config loading (RETENTION_DAYS, METRICS_RETENTION_DAYS) |\n\nThis architecture cleanly separates concerns: the registry declares intent, `RetentionPolicy` implements the algorithm, `retention.ts` orchestrates the job, and `auditRetentionPolicy.ts` shows how to apply it to compliance-sensitive data."}],"totalDurationMs":49741,"totalTokens":41331,"totalToolUseCount":19,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1294,"cache_read_input_tokens":37108,"output_tokens":2927,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1294},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
